\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} x^2 = \lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} x
((\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} x^2)/(\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} x)) = 1
\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} (x^2/x) = 1
\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty} x = 1
\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty}(x^2/x)
\lim_{x \rightarrow \infty}(x/1) = \lim_{x \rightarrow \infty}(x)
1
